2026-03-28T12:07:07.9315686Z             "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Changed email subject from `hpoll Daily Summary - DD Mon YYYY` to `Activity Summary - {Customer Name}`, removing the product prefix and date\r\n- Added `SummaryWindowOffsetHours` setting (default: 1) to `EmailSettings`, shifting all window boundaries by 1 hour (e.g. 01:00/05:00/09:00/13:00/17:00/21:00 instead of 00:00/04:00/08:00/12:00/16:00/20:00)\r\n- Replaced integer-division bucket alignment with a `Math.Floor`-based formula that correctly handles the offset, including the overnight wraparound case (e.g. midnight falling in a 21:00–01:00 window)\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Core/Configuration/CustomerConfig.cs` — added `SummaryWindowOffsetHours = 1` to `EmailSettings`\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Core/Interfaces/IEmailRenderer.cs` — updated doc comment to describe offset-based alignment\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Email/EmailRenderer.cs` — updated bucket-end calculation to use `Math.Floor` with offset\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Admin/Pages/Customers/Detail.cshtml.cs` — same bucket calculation update for admin preview\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Worker/Services/EmailSchedulerService.cs` — new subject format; removed unused `tz`/`localNow` variables\r\n- `src/Hpoll.Worker/Program.cs` — log new `summary_window_offset_hours` setting in system info\r\n- `tests/Hpoll.Core.Tests/EmailRendererTests.cs` — updated all window boundary assertions and test data to match new 1-hour offset\r\n- `tests/Hpoll.Core.Tests/ConfigurationValidationTests.cs` — added default check for `SummaryWindowOffsetHours`; updated zero-window-hours test (float division no longer throws)\r\n- `tests/Hpoll.Worker.Tests/EmailSchedulerServiceTests.cs` — updated subject assertion to match new format\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n- [ ] Verify emails arrive with subject `Activity Summary - {customer name}` (no date, no `hpoll` prefix)\r\n- [ ] Verify activity windows in the email are aligned to 01:00, 05:00, 09:00, 13:00, 17:00, 21:00 local time\r\n- [ ] Check admin portal customer detail page shows activity windows with the new boundaries\r\n- [ ] Confirm `Email__SummaryWindowOffsetHours` env var overrides the default offset\r\n- [ ] All 535 unit tests pass",
